transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, I need to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 1: No problem, I can help you.

Speaker 2: Can I have your phone number so I can pull up your account?

Speaker 1: 417-234-5583.

Speaker 2: Thank you, Dottie.

Speaker 1: Can you just confirm your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 12-30-1969.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: I see you're a VIP status customer.

Speaker 1: And how's the medication working out for you?

Speaker 2: It's working pretty good, but I just need to cancel it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I can't afford it right now

Speaker 1: and don't want it down my card.

Speaker 2: Yeah, not a problem.

Speaker 1: So with your VIP status,

Speaker 2: you don't have to have your refills on a monthly basis.

Speaker 1: What you can do and what a lot of people like to do

Speaker 2: is just go ahead and pause their refills for six months.

Speaker 1: That way it keeps your prescription active

Speaker 2: and just allows you to call in whenever you need a refill.

Speaker 1: I could pause that for you until July 31st of 2026.

Speaker 2: That's fine.

Speaker 1: And then it starts up again?

Speaker 2: Yeah, or you can just call and pause it further

Speaker 1: if you don't need a refill by then.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, do that, please.

Speaker 2: All right, no problem.

Speaker 1: All right, you're all set.

Speaker 2: How many more refills do I have on this one?

Speaker 1: You know, you have about six of them.

Speaker 2: Wow, okay.

Speaker 1: Well, yeah, pause it, please.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, not a problem.

Speaker 2: You're paused until 31st.

Speaker 1: Anything else I need to do?

Speaker 2: Nope, that's it.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you, have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too, bye.
